<item>
            <title>[LU-11849] lfs find ! --projid doesn&apos;t work as expected</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11849</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Somehow lfs find ! --projid &amp;lt;num&amp;gt; didn&apos;t work well and it is very easy to reproduce this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@exa4-1 client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lfs find --projid 1002 foor&lt;br/&gt;
foor/not-project&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@exa4-1 client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lfs find ! --projid 1002 foor&lt;br/&gt;
foor&lt;br/&gt;
foor/2.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/not-project      -------------&amp;gt; this should not be outputted here.&lt;br/&gt;
foor/4.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/3.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/5.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/1.file&lt;br/&gt;
Behavior I would expect would be something like the &apos;--ost&apos; case:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@exa4-1 client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lfs find ! --ost 0 foor&lt;br/&gt;
foor/3.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/5.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/1.file&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@exa4-1 client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lfs find  --ost 0 foor&lt;br/&gt;
foor/2.file&lt;br/&gt;
foor/not-project&lt;br/&gt;
foor/4.file&lt;/p&gt;</description>
